1. In a large saucepan heat oil and sauté onion, garlic and spices
2. Add washed lentils, water, tomatoes and soup and bring mixture to the boil
3. Reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes
4. Add zucchini and salt and simmer a further 5 minutes
Add salt as an ingredient? We often develop a taste for salt however too much
and too often can increase blood pressure and have a negative impact on bone
Try weaning yourself off salt - if at first you have 3 shakes on your meal
reduce this back to 2 shakes for a couple of months, then 1 shake and so on.
